<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416766>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 9. Parasabanema sene sp. n. In all illustrations of the synlophe in transverse section the dorsal aspect of the body is oriented towards the top of the page and the left side of the nematode to the left of the page. The dorsal and ventral (numbers with superscripts) ridges are numbered, as are the lateral rays of the bursa (right rays with superscripts). A. Female, anterior end lateral view, cervical vesicle bent dorsally; B. Male, cervical vesicle lateral view; C. Male, mid body transverse section; D. Female, mid body transverse section; E. Male, spicule anterior end; F. Male, spicule tips; G. Male, ventral view showing gubernaculum, spicule tips and genital cone; H. Female, towards posterior end transverse section; I. Female, posterior end lateral view showing ovejector; J. Male, bursa partially unrolled. Scale bars in µm: A. I, J, 50; B–H, 25." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4416766/files/figure.png" .

